Sentencas: In the present study, the performances of a single solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) and a micro-SOFC stack fueled with flame of combusting liquefied petroleum gas (LPG) were studied.
Titulo: Direct Flame SOFCs with La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-δ/Ni Coimpregnated Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia Anodes Operated on Liquefied Petroleum Gas Flame

Sentencas: La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-delta and Ni coimpregnated yttria-stabilized zirconia were used as the anode material of the direct-flame SOFC.
Titulo: Direct Flame SOFCs with La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-δ/Ni Coimpregnated Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia Anodes Operated on Liquefied Petroleum Gas Flame

Sentencas: The operation temperature of the cell can be sustained at 500-700 degrees C for the combustion of LPG.
Titulo: Direct Flame SOFCs with La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-δ/Ni Coimpregnated Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia Anodes Operated on Liquefied Petroleum Gas Flame

Sentencas: With the anode facing the LPG flame and the La0.8Sr0.2MnO3-delta cathode freely exposing to ambient air, the single cell exhibited an open-circuit voltage (OCV) of more than 0.85 V and the maximum power density (P-max) of 238 mW/cm(2).
Titulo: Direct Flame SOFCs with La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-δ/Ni Coimpregnated Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia Anodes Operated on Liquefied Petroleum Gas Flame

Sentencas: The micro-SOFC stack with three single cells connected in series demonstrated an OCV of 2.5 V and the maximum power output of 64 mW (corresponding to a P-max of 139 mW/cm(2)).
Titulo: Direct Flame SOFCs with La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-δ/Ni Coimpregnated Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia Anodes Operated on Liquefied Petroleum Gas Flame

Sentencas: The cell performance was found to be strongly influenced by the cell temperature.
Titulo: Direct Flame SOFCs with La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-δ/Ni Coimpregnated Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia Anodes Operated on Liquefied Petroleum Gas Flame

Sentencas: And the temperature is determined by cell position and gas composition.
Titulo: Direct Flame SOFCs with La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-δ/Ni Coimpregnated Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia Anodes Operated on Liquefied Petroleum Gas Flame

Sentencas: Additionally, the cell stability and carbon deposition after operation on the diffusion flame of the LPG were also tested.
Titulo: Direct Flame SOFCs with La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-δ/Ni Coimpregnated Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia Anodes Operated on Liquefied Petroleum Gas Flame
